Program description blurb for ppt.37:
Generally, business taxpayers that: (1) are engaged in a qualified activity; (2) hire five or more qualified employees;
and, (3) make an investment of at least $200,000 ($40,000 per qualified employee) in a qualified facility are entitled
to tax credits against the corporation or personal income taxes, gross receipts tax, and public utility tax. (Delaware Department of Revenue)

